Texas Rangers Defeat Tampa Bay Rays 4-3 to Win Game 3 of AL Playoff Series

-- B y   R o b   G l o s t e r
-- 
2011-10-04T01:00:04Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-04/texas-rangers-defeat-tampa-bay-rays-4-3-to-win-game-3-of-al-playoff-series.html
Mike Napoli hit a two-run homer and
 Josh Hamilton  added a two-run single in the Rangers’ four-run
seventh inning as Texas defeated the Tampa Bay Rays to take a 2-
1 lead in their best-of-five American League Division Series.  The New York Yankees are playing at the Detroit Tigers
tonight in Game 3 of the other AL Division Series, which is tied
1-1.  Rays starter  David Price  held the Rangers scoreless for six
innings until Napoli’s home run. Texas starter Colby Lewis
allowed just one hit in six innings, a home run leading off the
fourth inning by Desmond Jennings, in the Rangers’ 4-3 victory
at Tropicana Field in St. Petersburg, Florida.  Jennings also hit a home run against reliever Mike Adams
leading off the eighth inning for  Tampa Bay , which scored its
other run on a groundout in the seventh.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Rob Gloster at 
 rgloster@bloomberg.net  